==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Whimsey
<hw>Whim"sey</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To fill with whimseys, or
whims; to make fantastic; to craze.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To have a man's brain <qex>whimsied</qex> with his wealth.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Fletcher.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whimsical</ent>⟦br⟧
